    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="552"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d552">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d552fn1">Delivered to the British Embassy at Washington for
                        transmission to Churchill in Canada.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-30">August 30,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From the President to <gloss target="#t_CW1">Col. Warden.</gloss> Number 350.</p>
                <p>Perfectly delighted that <gloss target="#t_LW1">Lady Warden</gloss> can come too.
                    We will have a quiet family party. Elliot and Ruth<note n="2" xml:id="d552fn2"
                        >The Roosevelts’ son and daughter-in-law.</note> will be here and Margaret
                        Suckley<note n="3" xml:id="d552fn3">A cousin of Roosevelt.</note> and no one
                    else. The marvelous big fish dropped out of the clouds and we had two for
                    supper.</p>
            </div>
